NORMALISED EXTRACT:
Operator: a % b -> number
Definition: computes the remainder of the mathematical division of a by b following ECMAScript ToNumber coercion rules for numeric operands and using integer truncation toward zero when deriving the quotient. The result r satisfies: a = b * q + r where q is ToInteger(a / b) and r has the same sign as a (the dividend). If b is 0, result is NaN for Number arithmetic. Using BigInt operands uses BigInt remainder semantics; mixing BigInt and Number throws TypeError.

